    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "My 2ï¿ - I found about this change when I've tried to write a unit test for a JSON file. I wanted to check if property containing time conforms to specific format (ISO 8601/RFC 3339). I was using `[datetime]::TryParseExact` and couldn't figure out why it fails until I looked into the debugger and saw that the property was converted to `[dateime]` instead of being a plain string.\r\n\r\nI get how this could benefit round trip scenarios, but I wish that `ConvertFrom-Json` had an option to disable this behavior. Perhaps a `-Raw` switch?",
